CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, October 27, 1945, pg. 15, reads: "Intellectuals!  Students at Pitt gather at one of [the] focal points on the campus to discuss the weighty problems of the day.  Left to right: Frederick L. Marcus, New Kensington; Carl E. Redwood, Irwin; Warren H. Dorsey, 7741 Baxter Avenue, and George W. Rose of East Liberty. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Frederick L. Marcus, Carl E. Redwood, Warren H. Dorsey, and George W. Rose gathered on campus of University of Pittsburgh
